  "texts": [
    "The only thing to be checked is that the locally-defined objects behave well with respect to the transition maps, so that they glue to define a global object.",
    "More precisely, consider a bundle atlas {U i × N} i∈I for M adapted to H, with locally constant transition functions τ ij:U i ∩ U j → ρ(π 1 (B)) ⊂ Aut(N).Since N is simply-connected, there is a canonical Lie group isomorphism Aut(N) ≃ Aut(𝔫), φ → φ, and this defines a bundle atlas {U i × 𝔫} i∈I for adM, with transition functions τ ij.",
    "In each trivialisation U i × 𝔫, the derivation field D becomes D i: U i → Der(𝔫).",
    "For each t this gives exp(tD i): U i → Aut(𝔫), and under a change of trivialisation these change viaexp(tD i) = τ ij • exp(tD j) • τ -1 ij.",
    "Let ϕ i t ∈ Aut(N) be defined by ϕ i t = exp(tD i).Clearly, these transform viaϕ i t = τ ij • ϕ j t • τ -1 ij,andthus, for each t ∈ R, the locally-defined mapsU i × N → U i × N,(u, n) → (u, ϕ i t (u)) glue up to define a diffeomorphism ϕ t of M. This gives rise to a one-parameter group (ϕ t) t∈R of diffeomorphisms of M that are also twisted principal bundle isomorphisms covering the identity (see Section 2.1)."
